 problems and presents a sounder text than the ones established by previous editors; the critical apparatus is based on a fresh examination of the extant manuscripts and the indirect transmission, and on a careful evaluation of the philological studies which have appeared since Pithou’s editio princeps (1596).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Latin.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aFabeln. 4aPhaedrus. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aFables.  aPhaedrus.1 aZago, Giovanni, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311031632240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041054940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110410549423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110410549/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020